Two dimeters are often combined into an acatalectic tetrameter, and these tetrameters, anapaestici octonarii, sometimes form a system ending with a septenarius.

Anapaestic tetrameter catalectic verses, anapaestici septenarii, admit spondees anci dactyls promiscuously, even dactyls before anapaests.
